    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-11-30T20:22:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-11-30T20:22:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <head>235. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d235fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 303, Agency Files, <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Vol. IX. Secret; Exdis. Repeated to
                        Georgetown.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-12-01T01:22:00+00:00">December 1, 1971,
                        0122Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4657. Subj: <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> Succession: <persName
                        corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName> Candidacy. Ref: <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 4564.<note n="2" xml:id="d235fn2">Telegram
                        4564 f om <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> described a November 26
                        meeting between <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName>, in which <persName
                            corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> first mentioned that <persName
                            corresp="#p_RSS1">S.S. Ramphal</persName> was a candidate for
                        Secretary-General. <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> planned to
                        approach other Permanent Members and requested that his meeting with
                            <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> be considered “exploratory
                        and confidential” until further notice. (Ibid., RG 59, Central Files
                        1970–73, <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> 8–3)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Guyanan Perm Rep <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> called on
                            <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> Nov 30 to deliver <persName
                            corresp="#p_RSS1">S.S. Ramphal</persName>’s curriculum vitae and report
                        on his meetings with other four permanent members of <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                            >SC</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> said he had discussed
                            <persName corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName>’s availability for post
                        of <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> with the other <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                            >SC</gloss> members along lines of his discussion with <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> (reftel). <gloss target="#t_PRC1"
                            >PRC</gloss> Perm Rep <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Huang Hua</persName>
                        said <gloss target="#t_PRC1">PRC</gloss> was completely uncommitted on this
                        question at this time, but <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> had
                        definite impression Chinese were giving thought to the question of <gloss
                            target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> succession. <persName>Malik</persName>
                            (<gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>) said he would be glad to add
                            <persName corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName>’s name to list of ten or
                        so names currently being talked about. <persName>Malik</persName> noted,
                        however, there was no U (for <persName corresp="#p_TU1">U Thant</persName>)
                        on this list. <persName>Malik</persName> reportedly voiced opinion <persName
                            corresp="#p_TU1">Thant</persName> might accept interim reappointment.
                            <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DCM1">Del</persName> allegedly received suggestion of
                            <persName corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName>’s name with interest.
                            <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> did not report any French
                        reaction.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">Bush</persName> said <persName>Malik</persName>
                        was being consistent in continuing to talk about <persName corresp="#p_TU1"
                            >Thant</persName> staying on. Unfortunately, Soviets continue to be
                        evasive despite fact time was getting short. <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1"
                            >Bush</persName> said he was personally pleased to add <pb facs="0456"
                            n="419" xml:id="pg_419"/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName>’s name to list of potential
                        candidates. He told <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> he would
                        forward curriculum vitae to <gloss target="#t_DEPT1">Dept</gloss> and
                        assured <persName corresp="#p_TFH1">Talbot</persName> he would carefully
                        consider <persName corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName>’s
                        qualifications.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Copy curriculum vitae pouched <gloss target="#t_DEPT1">Dept</gloss>
                        attention <gloss target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss>.<note n="3" xml:id="d235fn3">Not
                            found.</note> Available biographic information on <persName
                            corresp="#p_RSS1">Ramphal</persName> requested.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGHW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Bush</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
